Subject:Re: [Fwd: Re: [Jukebox-list] Vinyl record]
On 11/8/12 7:08 PM, newtjr wrote:
> Ron and Jay, I have a Wurlitzer 3000 and W2610. newtjr

The small-hole 45 will play just fine on the 3000 without modifying the
record at all.  Behind the turntable is a solenoid with a small two-pin
light bulb.  Pull the light bulb out.  This will prevent the machine
from shifting to 33 RPM.

The 2610 may have a similar if not identical setup.


